Max Verstappen is a Dutch Formula One racing driver who currently competes for Red Bull Racing Honda. He was born on September 30, 1997 in Hasselt, Belgium, and is the son of former Formula One driver Jos Verstappen. Max made his Formula One debut with Toro Rosso in 2015 at the age of 17, becoming the youngest driver in the history of the sport. He moved to Red Bull Racing in 2016 and has since become one of the top drivers in Formula One, known for his aggressive driving style and impressive racecraft. As of my knowledge cutoff in September 2021, he had won 15 Grand Prix races and was a serious contender for the 2021 Drivers' Championship title.